        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 2:32PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 232 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Cheraw Municipal Airport, or 8 miles northwest of
Cheraw, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wallace.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
